TYPE SPECIMENS. —
Holotype
: BAR 758’00 – Partial skull with the complete face and the palate including the complete post-canine dentition on both sides except for the left P3/
. —
Paratypes
: BAR 756’00 , maxilla with I1/ and P3/-M3/
;
BAR 757’00 , partial skull with M2/-M3/ also with left P4/, right P3/-P4/ but damaged
;
BAR 759’00 , left maxilla with P3/-M3/
;
BAR 760’00 , left mandibular fragment with m/2-m/3 and broken m1/
;
BAR 761’00 , back of calvarium
;
BAR 762A’00 , the left maxilla with P4/-M3/, + BAR 762B’00 / OCO 1049’11 , right maxilla with P3/ and M1/-M3/
;
BAR 786’00 / BAR 1368’00 , left maxilla with M2/-M3/
;
BAR 1586’00 , an edentulous mandibular symphysis
;
OCO 608’10 , mandible with right p/3-m/3 and left i/2-m/3 and OCO 100’01 , a fragment of edentulous mandible
;
21 isolated teeth ( BAR 784’00 , BAR 785’00 , BAR 1214’00 , BAR 1369’00 , BAR 1584’00 , BAR 1585’00 , BAR 470’01 , BAR 1595’01 , BAR 1597’01 , BAR 250’03 , BAR 1190’03 , BAR 1381’03 , BAR 1382’03 , BAR 349’04 , BAR 351’04 , BAR910’04 , OCO 104’10 , OCO 105’10 , OCO 335’10 , OCO 101’11 and OCO 305’11 )
;
and four post-cranial bones ( BAR 757’00 , an axis vertebra, BAR 914’04 , a proximal extremity of a right metatarsal V, OCO 336’10 , a distal extremity of a left humerus, and OCO 102’11 , a distal extremity of a right humerus).

GEOLOGICAL AGE. — From the basal part of the Lukeino Formation, the Kapgoywa Member dated to the Late Miocene ( c. 6-5.7 Ma). ( Pickford & Senut 2001 ;
Sawada et al. 2002
).

